article.headline: SE Missouri State 77, Santa Barbara 75
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. (AP) -- Dainmon Gonner had 21 points and Brett Hale scored all 12 of his points in the last five minutes Sunday as Southeast Missouri State held off UC Santa Barbara 77-75 in the consolation game of the Montana DoubleTree Holiday Classic. Southeast Missouri State (3-1) trailed 56-51 with just over eight minutes to play when Brandon Griffin scored eight of his 14 points and Gonner added a 3-pointer to push Southeast Missouri to a 62-56 lead with 5:40 remaining. Hale then scored the Indians' next 11 points, answering three straight 3-pointers by UCSB (1-2). The last points in his run gave Southeast Missouri a 73-65 lead with 1:53 to go. Jacoby Atako, who led UCSB with 23 points, scored the team's final 10 points, including a basket with 15 seconds left to cut the margin to 75-72. Hale made a free throw with 14 seconds left and Terrick Willoughby added another with five seconds left. Atako hit his fourth 3-pointer at the buzzer. Casey Cook added 16 points for the Gauchos, who tied the game at 32 at halftime after falling behind 19-7 in the early going. Derek Winans also had 14 points for the Indians.
